                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The four Foreign Ministers held a brief meeting at which they noted that the
                    remaining unresolved points in the Protocol on the Termination of the Occupation
                    Regime in the Federal Republic of <pb facs="0354" n="1422" xml:id="pg_1422"/>
                    Germany and its five attached schedules had been resolved by a Working Group
                    made up of members of each of the four participating countries’ delegations. For
                    the text of the Protocol, see <ref target="#pg_1435">page 1435</ref>. A
                    three-page verbatim record of this meeting is in the Conference files, lot 60 D
                    627, CF 378; no telegraphic summary was found in Department of State files.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
